  "description": {
    "en-US": "Travel phrases for Taiwan with audio, built for EasyCard trips, TRA and HSR travel, hotel check-ins, night markets, and everyday service conversations.",
    "zh-CN": "中国台湾旅行短语卡，围绕 EasyCard、台铁与高铁、酒店入住、夜市和日常服务沟通等高频场景整理。"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en-US": "Built for Taiwan trips where airport MRT, TRA or HSR transfers, hotel counters, and night-market food stops all stack together. These cards help when you need quick Traditional Mandarin for station names, EasyCard questions, takeaway orders, or asking for a quieter room.",
    "zh-CN": "这套中国台湾短语适合那种机场捷运、台铁或高铁、酒店前台和夜市小吃会连着出现的旅行节奏。遇到要确认站名、EasyCard、外带需求，或者想要求一个安静一点的房间时，短语卡会很实用。"
  },
  "teaser": {
    "en-US": "Built for Taiwan EasyCard travel, TRA or HSR connections, hotel counters, and night-market ordering.",
    "zh-CN": "适合中国台湾的 EasyCard、台铁或高铁换乘、酒店柜台和夜市点餐沟通。"
  },
  "travelTips": {
    "en-US": [
      "Keep transport phrases ready for EasyCard questions, TRA or HSR transfers, and station exits before you leave the airport.",
      "Dining phrases matter most at breakfast shops and night markets when you want to ask for takeaway, no cilantro, or less ice.",
      "Traditional Mandarin signs are clear in Taiwan, but a phrase card still helps when you want to move quickly at counters or busy stations."
    ],
    "zh-CN": [
      "从机场进城前，最好先备好 EasyCard、台铁或高铁换乘，以及出入口相关短语。",
      "在早餐店和夜市里，餐饮短语最实用，尤其是打包带走、不要香菜和少冰这些需求。",
      "中国台湾的繁体中文标识通常很清楚，但在忙碌柜台或车站里，直接出示短语卡还是能明显加快沟通。"
    ]
  },
  "highlights": {
    "en-US": [
      "EasyCard, TRA, and night markets",
      "Breakfast shops, takeaway, and less ice",
      "Hotels, station exits, and HSR transfers"
    ],
    "zh-CN": [
      "EasyCard、台铁与夜市沟通",
      "早餐店、外带与少冰需求",
      "酒店、出入口与高铁换乘"
    ]
  },
