  "faq": [
    {
      "question": {
        "en-US": "Which phrase groups matter most for a Taiwan trip?",
        "zh-CN": "去中国台湾旅行时，最值得先准备哪几组短语？"
      },
      "answer": {
        "en-US": "Start with transport, dining, and hotel. That covers airport MRT, EasyCard, TRA or HSR, check-in, and most first-day food orders in Taiwan.",
        "zh-CN": "建议先看交通、餐饮和酒店三组，基本就能覆盖机场捷运、EasyCard、台铁或高铁、入住办理，以及第一天大部分点餐场景。"
      }
    },
    {
      "question": {
        "en-US": "Why keep phrase cards handy if Taiwan already uses Chinese characters?",
        "zh-CN": "既然中国台湾本来就用中文，为什么还值得准备短语卡？"
      },
      "answer": {
        "en-US": "Because you often need a fast, exact phrase at counters, stations, and night markets. Having the card ready is quicker than typing or rewording the same request.",
        "zh-CN": "因为很多场景需要的是一个很快、很准确的表达，比如柜台、车站和夜市。提前备好短语卡，通常会比现场打字或临时换说法更快。"
      }
    }
  ]
}
